args:
The Imperial Army mistakes the festival goods
for military supplies, and hopes to score a big
win by invading the town before it becomes the
site of an enemy base. When Cassandra and
Curran are unable to make them listen to
reason, the invasion begins in earnest.
What the hell are you talking about?!
So you intend to feign ignorance until the\nvery last, do you? Your guile is pointless;\nwe have you sussed out.

Then why don't you enlighten us, dearie?
I'm EVER so fascinated to know what
manner of nonsense you've cooked up
in that noggin of yours.
This here information was found out\nby the brave soldiers of the Northern Fort,\nwhich is us! And to prove it—
Recruit? Please don't surrender\nour intelligence to the enemy.
No, go on. I am curious to see how they\nexplain away what we have discovered.\n...As you were, recruit.
Oy, sir! See, a few days ago, we saw a\nbuncha merchants sneakin' in and out'a\nQuinbell over in Alberian territory, yeah?

Like, one of 'em was carryin' some kinda
mystery mineral from the mountains!
He had it in a box, like, so we couldn't
see it real well, but we knows it was there.

Anyways, we sniffed around and found out
that mountain has iron mines, which
means they've been sneakin' iron ore
into Quinbell! Pretty clever, eh?
I'd not heard about... Well, any of that.
Still playing the fool, I see. Very well.\nRecruit, tell him the best piece of\ninformation we discovered.
Sir, oy, sir! See, under orders from the\ncaptain there, I made for Quinbell what\nto conduct a little reconnaissance.
And when I gots there, I saw makeshift\ncamps set up all over town—plus a\ngiant watchtower right in the center!
NOW do you deny the truth of it?\nClearly, the town of Quinbell is being\nbolstered with a military presence.
You Alberian scum are secretly\nplanning to turn it into a fort!
Cor, they're speechless, Captain!\nYou struck 'em dumb, you did!
Heh. So I have. Now let me tell you\nWHY we have invaded your territory...
We plan to crush Alberia's new fort in\nQuinbell before it can be completed!
You've yet to station a full garrison there,\nwhich means it's practically undefended!

I should have been an aristocrat in the
capital, but political intrigue saw me
booted to this backwater—and now is
the chance for me to show my quality!
We will win a great victory and bid this\nhayseed place farewell for good and all!
THREE CHEERS FOR THE CAPTAIN!\nHIP HIP, HOORAY! HIP HIP, HOORAY!\nHIP HIP, HOORAY!
That...is amazing. I mean, it's also\ncompletely wrong, but still amazing.
Stop yer lyin', dog! We're onto you!
Oh, it's no lie. And if you need proof...\nGood merchant, might I trouble you to\nunpack some of your goods for these men?
Ha! Let's see what we have...
Oh ho! Arrows and bows! You have been\nunmasked by the very ploy you sought\nto save yourself with, you fool!
Calm down and look at them. ...Carefully.

Those arrows have no heads on them,
and the bows can fit in a single hand.
These are toys used by children to
fire at targets during the festival.
Yes, well, I suppose you would be hard-\npressed to do much damage with these...
But what about the iron ore, Captain?!\nThe stuff what from the mountains?!
ICE? Ha! And why in blazes would\nyour little town be importing ICE?!
There's a special Hinomotoan treat made\nby shaving ice with a small knife before\ndrizzling syrup on top of it.
Oh, it is. And now that you know,\nyou can hurry up and—
Very clever, the both of you...and yet there\nare still holes in this story of yours.
There is no way to spin your camps and\nwatchtower as being anything other than\nthe bones of a new fortress!
Except that what you saw aren't ＂camps＂\nor a ＂watchtower.＂ They're a festival stage\nand a bunch of stalls and food carts.

You did the recon, yes? Did you not notice
how these supposed military installations
were ornamented with all manner of
gaudy, merrymaking decorations?
Ya mean all them red and white steamers\nand lanterns they had on 'em?
Oy, sir! Sorry, sir! Thought they were for\nraising morale and the like, sir!
WHY WOULD THEY MAKE THEIR\nWATCHTOWER FLASHY TO BOOST\nMORALE?! WHAT ARMY DOES THAT?!
Perhaps you want to reconsider this\n＂intelligence＂ of yours, dearie.
Captain, I think it might be better\nfor us to withdraw at this point.
Given that this is a once-a-year festival,\nwe will grant mercy and... Hmm?
Oh, those are just test firings for the\npyroblossoms. Looks like we're going\nto see some real good stuff tonight.
What a perfect match for\nthe lantern ceremony!
Oh, I am well aware, recruit.
What are you driving at here?
That waaaaas...A PRACTICE RUN\nFOR A MAGICAL ATTACK!
Whatever are you on about?! Those are\npyroblossoms—harmless light mana.
Mana? Sorcery! WITCHCRAFT!\nAh HA! I KNEW it!
No festival uses magic that causes huge,\nflashy explosions over a wide area!\nWho has EVER heard of such a thing?!
Oh, you can't wheedle your way out of\nthis wasp's nest. ...You there! Seize them!
The rest of you, down the highway!\nWe're going to destroy that enemy fort!
Well, THIS took a very bad turn.\nMake for the woods, you two!
